---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const lastUpdated = "February 5, 2026";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="PrivacyFix privacy policy. We practice what we preach - minimal data collection, no tracking cookies, no data sales."
>
  <article class="py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <header class="mb-12">
          <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)]">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
        </header>

        <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
          <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-emerald-500/10 border border-emerald-500/20 mb-8">
            <p class="text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-300 font-medium mb-2">
              We practice what we preach.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)]">
              A privacy tools website that doesn't respect your privacy would be hypocritical.
              We collect minimal data, use no tracking cookies, and never sell your information.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Information We Collect</h2>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Analytics Data (Anonymous)</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            We use <a href="https://umami.is" class="text-emerald-500 hover:text-emerald-600">Umami</a>, a privacy-focused,
            cookie-free analytics platform. Umami collects:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            <li>Page views and referrer URLs</li>
            <li>Country (derived from IP, IP not stored)</li>
            <li>Device type, browser, and operating system</li>
            <li>Session duration</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            <strong>What Umami does NOT collect:</strong> Personal identifiers, IP addresses (they're discarded immediately),
            tracking cookies, or any data that could identify you personally.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Tool Data (Local Only)</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            Our privacy tools (Privacy Audit, Opt-Out Tracker, etc.) process all data locally in your browser.
            <strong>Your data never leaves your device</strong> and is never sent to our servers.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            <li>Audit responses are processed client-side only</li>
            <li>Tracker data is stored in your browser's localStorage</li>
            <li>You can clear this data at any time through your browser settings</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Error Tracking</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            We use <a href="https://sentry.io" class="text-emerald-500 hover:text-emerald-600">Sentry</a> to track
            technical errors. When an error occurs, Sentry may collect:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            <li>Error messages and stack traces</li>
            <li>Browser and device information</li>
            <li>Page URL where the error occurred</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            This helps us fix bugs quickly. No personal data is included in error reports.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Information We Do NOT Collect</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            <li>Names, email addresses, or contact information (unless you email us)</li>
            <li>IP addresses (anonymized immediately by our analytics)</li>
            <li>Tracking cookies or advertising identifiers</li>
            <li>Data from our privacy tools (stays in your browser)</li>
            <li>Browsing history beyond our site</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Cookies</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            We do not use tracking cookies. The only data stored in your browser is:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            <li><strong>Theme preference:</strong> Light/dark mode setting (localStorage)</li>
            <li><strong>Tool data:</strong> Your opt-out tracker progress, if you use it (localStorage)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            You can clear this data anytime in your browser settings.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            We use the following third-party services:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            <li><strong>Cloudflare:</strong> Hosting and CDN (may collect access logs temporarily)</li>
            <li><strong>Umami:</strong> Privacy-focused analytics (self-hosted, no cookies)</li>
            <li><strong>Sentry:</strong> Error tracking (no personal data)</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Affiliate Links</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            Some links on this site are affiliate links. When you click them and make a purchase, we may earn a commission
            at no extra cost to you. This helps fund the site.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            We only recommend products we believe are genuinely useful. Affiliate relationships do not influence our
            recommendations or reviews.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Your Rights</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            Depending on your location, you may have rights under GDPR, CCPA, or other privacy laws:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request what data we have about you (likely none)</li>
            <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of any data we hold</li>
            <li><strong>Opt-out:</strong> You can block our analytics with any ad blocker</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            To exercise these rights, email us at <a href="mailto:privacy@getprivacyfix.com" class="text-emerald-500 hover:text-emerald-600">privacy@getprivacyfix.com</a>.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            We may update this policy occasionally. Changes will be posted here with an updated date.
            Significant changes will be highlighted on the site.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Contact</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
            Questions about this privacy policy? Email us at
            <a href="mailto:privacy@getprivacyfix.com" class="text-emerald-500 hover:text-emerald-600">privacy@getprivacyfix.com</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
